3.02	Kam%C4%81l_al-D%C4%ABn_al-F%C4%81ris%C4%AB	Kamāl al-Dīn al-Fārisī	Kamal al-Din Hasan ibn Ali ibn Hasan al-Farisi or Abu Hasan Muhammad ibn Hasan (1267– 12 January 1319, long assumed to be 1320)) (Persian: ‎) was a prominent Persian born in Tabriz, Iran. He made two major contributions to science, one on optics, the other on number theory. Farisi was a pupil of the great astronomer and mathematician Qutb al-Din al-Shirazi, who in turn was a pupil of Nasir al-Din Tusi.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/c/c5/Kamal-1.jpg/400px-Kamal-1.jpg
